gfx906-fa-vllm contributors
===========================

  Nick <nick413@gmail.com>

Upstream project
----------------

This repository is a downstream fork of:

  mixa3607/ML-gfx906  —  https://github.com/mixa3607/ML-gfx906
                         (C) Mikhail Aksenov (@mixa3607)

Specifically, we build on top of the upstream Docker image:

  docker.io/mixa3607/vllm-gfx906:0.19.1-rocm-7.2.1-aiinfos

which bundles ROCm 7.2.1, PyTorch 2.9 and vLLM 0.19.1 patched for gfx906
(AMD MI50 / MI60 / Radeon VII). All of the underlying ROCm / PyTorch / vLLM
work in that image is @mixa3607's, not ours — this fork only adds the
custom attention backend, HIP kernels and the `vllm.general_plugins` entry
point that wires them into vLLM.

Acknowledgements
----------------

  @mixa3607              —  upstream ML-gfx906 stack (ROCm, PyTorch, vLLM images)
  llama.cpp project      —  original FlashAttention Q8_0 kernel design (MIT)
  vLLM project           —  paged KV cache layout, AttentionImpl API, plugin system
